result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

The defendant Nicholas Allen Yenter was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).
  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Deferred Agreement in effect in Count 1 of the Information for the duration of Probation.  Matter of returning Defendant's PlayStation to be discussed/considered.  1 day credit if revoked.

miscConds.notes:
$1,110 represents restitution plus $111 restitution surcharge.  Joint and Several.
Pursuant to 2nd Amended Restitution Order (DOC-31) dated 08/05/2014, $110 represents restitution owed plus $11 restitution surcharge.  Defendant had a cash bond posted that was applied to the amount of restitution.
Pursuant to 3rd Amended Restitution Order (DOC-31) dated 02/17/2015, $110 represents restitution plus $111 restitution surcharge.  Defendant had a cash bond posted that was applied to the amount of restitution.

Plus supervision fees.    If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due. All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.    $10 represents the mandatory statutory surcharge for 943 property crimes.
Any assessment and counseling as required and follow through and complete all required treatment.
Not to possess or consume any alcohol or illegal drugs.    Not to go on any premises where primary purpose is the sale of alcohol.    Not to possess any drug paraphernalia.

timeConds.notes: Pursuant to an Order dated May 22, 2014, Defendant to serve 30 days in jail beginning on the date of the signing of the Order (5/21/14), huber privileges are granted. (see attached order)
